<SLUG> BC-GIVING-THANKS-II-1STLD-WRITETHRU-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A BULLET RICOCHETS OFF A CELL PHONE AND AN OFFICER IS ONLY GRAZED 
</HEADLINE>
  (DELETES names of officers in grafs 2, 5 and 6 because they work
undercover) 
(DW) 
 By JAYSON BLAIR   c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A plainclothes officer who was shot at during an
undercover drug operation in the Bronx late Tuesday night escaped
serious injury when a bullet ricocheted off his cellular telephone
and grazed his stomach, officials said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The officer, whose name was not released because he works under-
cover, was wounded when three men tried to rob him and another
officer during an undercover sale of cocaine that the police had
hoped would help build a case against a drug organization,
officials said. He was listed in stable condition at Jacobi Medical
Center Wednesday night, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Three men were arrested on attempted murder and attempted
robbery charges, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The incident occurred at about 11:50 p.m. in an apartment in the
South Bronx. Police officials said that three suspected drug
dealers began firing in an apparent attempt to rob the two
officers.
</P>
<P>
   A bullet that probably would have struck the officer in the
stomach bounced off his cellular telephone and only grazed him,
Police Commissioner Howard Safir said outside the hospital
Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
   The sergeant's partner, whose name also was not released, was
struck over the head with a pistol, but was able to fire eight
shots with his 9-millimeter handgun, striking one of the
assailants, officials said. The officer who had been shot fired two
rounds from his Glock handgun before backup officers arrived and
arrested the suspects, officials added. Investigators said it was
unclear Wednesday who shot the officer.
</P>
<P>
   The three Bronx men who were arrested were identified by the
police as Shane Palmer, 28; Raymond Thomas, 22; and Shawn Howell,
21, who was shot in the left leg.
</P>
<P>
   Howell was in stable condition at Lincoln Hospital, officials
added. Investigators said that a 9-millimeter handgun and a knife
were found at the scene.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
