<HEADLINE>
GUARD AT EMPIRE STATE BUILDING ACCUSED OF SEXUAL ABUSE OF BOY
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Ga.)   (rk) 
 By   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A security guard at the Empire State Building was
arrested Wednesday night after a 14-year-old boy from Georgia told
the authorities that the guard had sexually abused him in a
stairwell, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   The boy, who was visiting the building with a tour group, became
separated from his companions around 6 p.m. and found himself in a
stairwell three flights below the 86th-floor observation deck, said
Detective Robert Samuel, a police department spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   There, the boy told the police, he was confronted by the guard,
Taher Patwary. The boy told the police that Patwary touched him
above the waist and made suggestive comments, Samuel said.
</P>
<P>
   The boy then walked away, took the elevator down to the lobby,
found his group and reported the incident to them and to a police
officer. Patwary, 43, of Brooklyn, was arrested and charged with
second-degree sexual abuse and endangering the welfare of a child,
both misdemeanors, Samuel said.
</P>
<P>
   Patwary's brother, Abdul Rob, said that Patwary had arrived from
Bangladesh 10 years ago and had been working at the Empire State
Building for five months.
</P>
<P>
   The police said that Patwary had no prior arrests.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
